instruction: Create a short story about a person discovering a new planet.
output: Jane was an astronomer who had devoted her life to searching the night sky for clues about the universe beyond our solar system. One night, while she was doing her regular observation, she spotted something very strange in the sky—it was a bright light in an unexpected location. She quickly realized that she was looking at a new planet, one that had never been seen before! Jane was filled with excitement, and immediately began taking notes and photographs of the newfound planet. From that moment forward, she had made a new purpose in her life: to learn as much as possible about the mysterious planet she had discovered.
